The article is a press briefing about President Obama's visit to Afghanistan. The President was moved by his interactions with the troops and their concern for their families back home. He had a phone call with President Karzai, where they discussed the security transition and the enduring commitment to Afghanistan. The President also visited the hospital and met with wounded soldiers and awarded Purple Hearts. Due to bad weather, the planned visit to the embassy and the SVTC with Karzai had to be cancelled. The briefing also mentioned that the President called Prime Minister Netanyahu to offer condolences and assistance regarding the fires in Israel. The United States is providing fire-retardant chemicals, technical assistance teams, and mobilizing international guard members to help fight the fires.